"sysstat" is a system activity viewer and logger.

It is used to monitor system performance and usage activity.

It collects information from /proc, the kernel, and/or
external utilities, and displays summary information,
as well as log files of past activity.

The package also collects information from the cpufreq
module, even without being loaded, if there is such a
module on the system.

The package also monitors CPU frequency scaling,
acpi
